                                    <p style="text-align:justify">

                                      <strong>Overview</strong>
                                      <br>
                                      Research funding organizations aim to maximize the impact of their research grants to advance knowledge and meet their institutional mission.  Return on research investment is challenged by dysfunctional incentives for researchers, dependence on outdated methods of scientific communication, lack of infrastructure to connect and support the entire research lifecycle, and lack of standards in policies and practices for promoting research transparency and reproducibility.  
                                      <br><br>
                                      <strong>Purpose</strong>
                                      <br>
                                      Emerging good practices are providing opportunities for funders to improve research efficiency and nudge the incentives toward a more open, reproducible research culture.  This meeting will gather representatives of leading research funding organizations and other stakeholders to share knowledge and promote community standards for maximizing the effective stewardship of research dollars for advancing the social good.
                                      <br><br>
                                      <strong>Attendees</strong>
                                      <br> 
                                      Representatives of private and federal funders who want to share good practices and/or learn about what leading edge funding organizations are doing on reproducibility and transparency.  In particular, meeting topics will be highly suitable for representatives of funders with responsibilities for grantee policies and procedures, grant management, program officers, and senior executives.
                                      <br><br>
                                      <strong>Goals</strong>
                                      <br>
                                      <ol>
                                        <li>Helping to establish shared expectations among funders for grantees</li>
                                        <li>Providing resources for funders to update their policies and practices</li> 
                                        <li>Sharing experiences and good practices among funders and researchers</li>
                                        <li>Formulating collaborations and partnerships with mission-aligned stakeholders, such as between funders and journals/publishers</li>
                                        <li>Exploring innovative strategies and emerging trends for research transparency and reproducibility</li>
                                      </ol> 
                                      <br>
                                      <h4><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1E4hFiVcN89RTUXIHa-BWE5gZr-SMdnFuvlDAfMmLGJU/edit?ts=57b5fa01">Read the full agenda here.</a></h4></p>
                                      


